OL,5, One of the UK's most successful        
OL,6, children's authors says schools should 
OL,7, teach black history all year round.    
OL,9,FMalorie Blackman said history lessons  
OL,10,Fshould tell "the whole truth" of the   
OL,11,FBritish Empire, such as Britain's role 
OL,12,Fin the transatlantic slave trade.      
OL,14,FSchools in England are not currently   
OL,15,Frequired to teach any black history.   
OL,17,FAdding it to the curriculum would help 
OL,18,Fprevent those speaking out against     
OL,19,Fracism being accused of "race-baiting",
OL,20,Fthe former children's laureate said.   
